  <prompt>
    Implement a GET /api/open-links endpoint in the Spe.Bff.Api that accepts a driveItemId, 
    retrieves the document's web URL and MIME type from Microsoft Graph, and returns the 
    desktop protocol URL using the DesktopUrlBuilder utility. Follow ADR-001 Minimal API patterns.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in ASP.NET Core Minimal APIs and Microsoft Graph SDK.
    Follow ADRs strictly. Prefer minimal abstractions per ADR-010.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A working GET /api/open-links?driveItemId={id} endpoint that returns JSON with the 
    desktop protocol URL, properly authenticated and following Minimal API patterns.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The FileViewer PCF needs to get the desktop protocol URL (ms-word:, etc.) for a document
      so it can launch the native Office application. The BFF is the appropriate place to call
      Microsoft Graph and construct the URL, keeping the PCF thin.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Spe.Bff.Api/Program.cs (modify)</file>
      <file>src/shared/Spaarke.SharePointEmbedded/Utilities/DesktopUrlBuilder.cs (use)</file>
      <file>src/shared/Spaarke.SharePointEmbedded/SpeFileStore.cs (reference)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Use Minimal API pattern - no controllers</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Authentication handled by endpoint filters (added in task 003)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Inject only what's needed - prefer thin service layer</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Must return 404 if driveItemId not found</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Must return 400 if driveItemId parameter missing</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
