  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">
      GET /api/open-links?driveItemId={valid-id} returns 200 with JSON containing desktopUrl.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      GET /api/open-links without driveItemId returns 400 Bad Request.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      GET /api/open-links?driveItemId={invalid-id} returns 404 Not Found.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Endpoint requires authentication (returns 401 without token).
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Response includes desktopUrl, webUrl, and mimeType fields.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      For Word documents, desktopUrl starts with "ms-word:ofe|u|".
    </criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Reference spec.md Section 5.1 for endpoint specification.
    
    Response DTO structure:
    public record OpenLinksResponse(
        string? DesktopUrl,
        string WebUrl,
        string MimeType
    );
    
    Graph API call pattern:
    var driveItem = await graphClient.Drives["{driveId}"]
        .Items[driveItemId]
        .GetAsync();
    
    Note: May need to determine driveId from context or pass it as parameter.
    Check how other endpoints handle this.
